inn1.comm: bowls it outside off, Azhar presses forward and defends to covers
good length, angling in on off and middle, gets forward and blocks comfortably
holding its line outside off, Azhar drops it in front of covers and wants a single but Sharjeel isn't too keen to sprint across
slightly shorter and outside off, stays on the backfoot and punches to mid-on
fires a tempter on the fifth stump channel, Azhar shoulders arms
angles it into the pads, tucked off them to deep backward square leg, quiet start to the game
on the money straight away, good length outside off, defended off the front foot back down the pitch
short ball, fires it down the leg side
fires it full on off, gets forward and works it to covers
very full and wide outside off, gets across and mistimes the drive to covers
short of good length, angling down, tucked away to deep backward square leg
very full ball on the corridor, squeezes it out and the ball rolls back down the ground
angles it across the left-hander who looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge to the third man boundary
bowls it full and down the leg side, tries to flick but can't get anywhere near it and Ramdin has no chance of getting his hands to it despite putting in the dive
stays in the crease and tries to defend to the off side but gets a thick inside edge that takes the ball to square leg
short of good length, jumps up to ride the extra bounce and tucks it away to the leg side
full and angling in, uss the drift to clip it away off the pads to the deep midwicket region, the ball is pulled back before the ropes

full and wide, too much width given and Sharjeel throws his hands at it, tries to go big over the in-field on the off side and goes at it with hard hads. But he ends up slicing it and the ball goes off the outer half of the bat
swipes across the line and does it effectively. It was full and outside off and Sharjeel fetches it from outside off and hammers it through the midwicket region
that's way too easy for Sharjeel. Bowled very full and right in the slot. Keeps his front foot movement to the minimum to give him enough room to free his arms, whacks it over long-off
tries to tuck it away but wears it on the pad and the ball goes away behind square
flicks it away to midwicket

short of a length, tries to open the face of his bat and run it down to third man, but point runs across and cuts it off, fires a direct hit and they think of taking a run off the deflection but eventually decide against it
hits the deck hard and Azhar rides the bounce before fending off to the leg side
back of a length and drifting in, gets the front leg across and pulls it away to deep midwicket
turns it away to fine leg
back of a length and nipping back in late, stays in the crease and runs it down to third man by opening the face of his bat
fuller ball, holding its line outside off, comes forward and taps it. Thinks of a quick single but doesn't take it as point swoops down on the ball
short ball and too straight. It's not very wide but Sharjeel still manages to get into a comfortable position and swivels around and pulls to deep square leg
more width on offer this time but it is not as short this time and Sharjeel doesn't middle his pull

plumb. It's a good length ball that nips back in, Azhar looks to work it slightly across the line and misses. He is rapped on the pads and that looks pretty plumb. Umpire raises his finger quickly and Azhar has a word with the non-striker before opting for the review. Replays show that the ball would hit the stumps flush and the decision is upheld
good length outside off, stays in the crease and bunts it to the off side

Sharjeel throws it away. Alzarri hits the deck hard and lands a length ball. Sharjeel looks to slog powerfully across the line and doesn't get hold of it. It's caught at mid-on. Joseph has his maiden ODI wicket
shorter ball, Malik gets outside of the line of the ball late and it is called a wide
back of a length around off, goes back in his crease and defends it back to the bowler
full and angling in, looks to clip it away off the toes but can't beat the fielder at midwicket
runs it down to third man and jogs across for the single
fuller ball on the fourth stump channel, waits for it in the crease before tapping it to covers
tucked with the angle to square leg, the fielder at midwicket runs across and cuts it off
shapes back in late. It's a good length ball outside off and Azam is on to neither foot and sticks his bat out, the ball beats the edge on its way to the wicketkeeper
short of a length, punched off the backfoot to point
effort ball, gets it to jag back in late, works it to mid-on
fuller ball that spits back in, nudged to midwicket
fuller ball, driven to mid-on
straight ball on a length, presses forward and presents the full face of his bat as he defends
good length ball, drifting in from outside off, tucked away to deep square leg
good length in and around off, no movement this time, runs it down to third man off the open face of his bat
good length ball, hits the deck hard, so it bounces well, shifts back in the crease to ride it before blocking it back to the bowler
presses forward and pushes it to covers
fuller ball, angling in on off, presents the full face of his bat and pushes it to mid-on
back of a length ball, tucks it with the angle straight to square leg
short ball and width on offer, slaps it away and splits the gap between point and cover-point perfectly
short ball, keeps low outside off, slashes and is beaten by the lack of bounce
fuller ball on off, pushs it on the front foot towards mid-on where the fielder dives to make the save
short ball, backs away to cut but it keeps a tad low and moves back in late, can't make any contact
tries to flick and gets it off the inside edge to deep backward square leg
bowls it on the corridor outside off, presses forward and defends to the off side
tries to flick and gets a leading edge that goes past the fielder at point to deep backward point
defended back to the bowler
angling down leg, uses the drift and tucks it behind square on the leg side
good length around off, stays in the crease and works it to midwicket. Fielder at mid-on runs across and picks it up
short of a length on off, holding its line, jumps up to ride the bounce and drops it in front of mid-on before scampering across for the single
short and angling down, pulls with the angle and the ball goes on the bounce to deep backward square leg

the deep square leg fielder went the wrong way, and so a boundary has been conceded when it should have been two at most. This one was a length delivery coming back in, he simply hopped across to whip it away off his hip. Sweet timing
draws him forward, defended off the front foot
gets a good stride forward and caresses that wide of cover for an easy single
leg-stump half-volley which he tried to play a lot squarer, hit straight to midwicket
fetches a wild slog from outside off, gets a thick inside edge to deep backward square leg
looked to hit it too hard, mistimes an attempted lofted hit to mid-off.
slides one into the pads, worked to deep midwicket
too full on middle and leg, flicked with the spin to the on side as they amble a single
this one goes straight on after pitching on middle, punched wide of midwicket
slow turn, he didn't get to the pitch of the ball but still went through with a wristy flick past midwicket
opens the bat face to dab that shortish delivery to point
looks to run that down to third man but Big Benn stops at at first slip.
looks to force it back past the bowler to mid-off, ends up hitting it straight to Carlos
whips a length ball angling into middle towards midwicket
nearly found Benn at midwicket. Fetches that whip from outside off, luckily for him, it fell short of the man there. He took it on the bounce
opens the bat face and uses the pace to run that down to third man
tight line on middle, floats it at length, worked to the man at mid-on, who is inside the ring. Not much bounce on this surface

this has come out of nowhere. He steps out and lofts the length ball over the infield. He made it look really easy. It was a simply shimmy down the pitch to meet the ball irrespective of how short or full it was. Intent was the key there
tucked wide of Pollard at midwicket for a quick single
plays back to a full delivery on off, dabbed
this time he picks the gap at short third man, sliding stop by Carlos Brathwaite who anticipated that shot and was off the blocks quickly
steered straight to backward point. It was fired in once again from Narine
gets to the pitch of the ball and turns it with the spin to long-on
short, wide and he's crunched that off the back foot to deep point

big mix-up, but no damage done in the end.  Azam, who played a short-arm jab towards deep midwicket, was guilty of staying put and admiring his shot even as Malik completed the single. It should have been two, and so he turned to come back, only to see Azam put his hand out late. Another second and he could have been run out at the striker's end
worked off his hip towards deep square leg, Malik wanted the second again, only to be sent back
excellent use of the feet. It was short of length once again, sitting up nicely for Malik to hit through the line as he stepped out. Swung like a golfer to get the elevation and clear the infield
floats a leg-cutter on middle from wide of the crease, worked wide of midwicket
fetches a pull from outside off, down to deep midwicket
angles a full ball on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
too easy, just a simple push off the back foot to beat the infield on the leg side. They jog across for a single
punched back to the bowler
sharp turn back into middle, it kept a touch low as well, worked behind square leg
flays that on the up, but can't find the gap behind point. Was hit really hard.
appeal for lbw. Was it the knuckle ball? This one breaks back in to hit the inside edge as he prodded forward
gets outside the line of the stumps to work it with the spin to midwicket
gets forward and defends it to cover
nearly chopped on. This didn't rise at all, and got the bottom edge as he tried to force it past cover

pulled, and pulled well. It wasn't a full-blooded one, but he still packed a punch as he split the gap between midwicket and mid-on. Didn't  bounce as much as Carlos wanted, and at his pace, it was a gift
too full on the pad, flicked to long-on as they amble a single
punched wide of midwicket for an easy single
slower delivery outside off, squeezed wide of backward point
driven past the bowler for an easy single
punched back to the bowler
lunges forward to dab that gently to the off side
Narine can't put his hand out to stop that firm drive back down the ground, easy single to long-on
gets across the stumps to work it to midwicket
drilled down the ground to long-off
driven inside-out to wide long-off to bring up the 100

friendly full toss that will be put away most times. Malik gave him the charge and swung across the line to muscle that over long-on. Could have hit it anywhere, really and he chose the smallest boundary. Neat execution
appeal for caught behind as Malik is beaten fair and square. It drifted back in and spun past Malik's feeble push.  Holder decides against the review.  S Ravi, the umpire in question
stretches forward and blocks
much better from Benn, bowls it at a good angle, from wide of the crease, forces Malik to press forward and block
quicker one on middle and leg, squeezed to long-on
tossed up outside off, defended back to the bowler
worked with the spin to long on for an easy single
width outside off, crunched to deep point
delivers this on the stumps from wide of the crease, steered to point
cuts and misses. This one skid through after pitching outside
gets outside the line of the stumps to work it to long-on
floated up on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
good use of the feet. It's flighted up on middle stumps channel, gets under it and makes room to give himself enough room before lifting it straight down the ground
pushed through quicker, defended off the backfoot back to the bowler
tucks to midwicket. Azam sets off for the single but it was never there as the ball went straight to the fielder there
tries to flick it to the leg sid and misses, appeal for lbw but not given. It would have missed leg stump
flighted at the stumps, played back to the bowler
full and wide, gives him enough room to free his arms and he drills it to sweeper coer. Two fielders converge on the ball and it is stopped before the ropes
pushed through flat and quick, eased down to long-on
backs away and opens the face of his bat to short third man
gets forward and pushes it to long-off
full and wide, creams it through covers and this time the ball travels all the way to the sweeper cover fence
short and wide, slaps it but straight to the fielder at cover-point
turns it behind to square leg

pitched up outside off, Azam eases it away through extra cover. Didn't try to hit it hard at all, so much so that it didn't look like a four, but the timing was so good it beats the fielder running in from long-off to the boundary
pushed through quicker, defended off the front foot to mid-off
advances down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
fuller and angled in to leg stump, backs away and drives it to long-off
works it through covers for a brace, sweeper cover runs to his left to field it
pitched up outside off, eased down to long-off
fired quick and at a flatter trajectory, pushed down to long-on
gives it a little air, Malik presses forward and drives past the diving cover fielder
flat and short of a length, punched off the backfoot to long-on
very full ball, driven easily to long-off to bring up his half-century
flighted on leg stump and turns away, comes forward and pushes uppishly, done in slightly by the turn there
very full and angling in, defended on the front foot to the off side
flighted on off, driven to long-off
pushed through quicker and drifting in to the pads, nudged with the angle easily to the leg side

advances down the track and creams a straight boundary, and that's fifty for Malik as well as the century of the partnership. Gets right to the pitch of the ball and plays it with a slightly angled bat, lot of power there and it bursts right past the bowler
fired on middle and leg, defended to the on side
length ball, angling in to the pads, tucked wide of mid-on
short of a length ball, angling in, tucked away to deep midwicket
short ball, pulled hard to deep midwicket, man there, so it will only be a single
another short of a length ball that is angled in to the right-hander, it goes down the leg side and is called a wide
persists with the shorter length, but it is outside off this time, taps it off the backfoot and drops it in front of cover for a quick single
good length outside off, punched to the left of extra cover
pushes him back with a back of a length ball, easily blocked off the backfoot
pushed to long-off
loopy delivery on the stumps, defended on the front foot to the right of the bowler
advances down the track and lifts him for a huge straight six. It was nicely flighted and Malik gets right on top of that before clearing the straight boundary. That was towering

comes down the track again and it's flatter this time but gets the maximum result nonetheless. It was loopy and flighted in on leg stump. Malik makes room and gets to the pitch of it before lofting it

make that a hat-trick. Benn doesn't learn from his mistakes. Angles it in to the right-hander again and gives a lot of flight. Malik was ready for it and comes down the track and gets it over deep midwicket. This is the biggest of the three and the ball has actually gone out of the stadium to the roads. 103 metres! A fan jumps across and braves the traffic to fetch the ball. Kudos to him!
advances down the ground and targets the other side of the boundary this time, doesn't get the elevation desired. It is hammered to long-off
fired in on the pads, tucked away to deep midwicket
shorter ball, stays in the crease and opens the face of his bat to run it down to third man
shorter ball, angling in, swivels around and pulls it to deep backward square leg
good length on off, defended to mid-on
offers a lot of width and Azam slashes hard, the ball goes through extra cover region and sweeper cover runs across and cuts it off
short ball, looks to pull but doesn't get it where he desired to, miscues it to mid-on and he lets out a yell to show his disappointment at missing out on that one
fuller ball outside off, presses forward and pushes it to mid-off
fuller and wider, presses forward and taps it to covers and takes off for a quick single
and the flurry continues. It is full and wide and Azam opens up his arms and creams it inside-out, the ball goes uppishly over extra cover. "It hurts to watch this," says Viv Richards on air
good length ball outside off, stabs it to backward point
angled in from outside off, tucked away for an easy single to deep midwicket
very full, almost a yorker on leg stump, clipped away to short fine leg
keeps it tight on the stumps, turns it away to backward square leg
shifts across in his crease and gets it away to square leg
flatter ball on the pads, worked with the turn to fine leg. Deep backward square leg has cover quite some ground, so they have enough time to take two
eases it down to long-on
flatter and full outside off, advances down the track and whips it behind square on the leg side
nearly chopped on. Stays in the crease and looks to defend but gets an inside edge and the ball narrowly misses the stumps. He was on to neither foot there
back of length delivery outside off, punched to cover point
to easy, friendly length ball on middle, bunted down to long-on for an easy single
pulled into the gap at deep backward square leg, excellent running
gently dabs the incoming delivery
half-volley on the pads, he tickles it down to fine leg where the fielder had a lot of work to do to come around and stop that
opens the bat face to run it down to third man for an easy single
cuts, but straight to short third man
makes a bit of room and crunches it to deep point
gets to the pitch of the ball and works it down to long-on for an ambled single
flatter one on middle, punched to Benn at extra cover

sees the ball tossed up over his eye-line and comes down to a delightful thump over midwicket. Gets down on one knee, underneath the flight and then the perfectly timed sweep. It was far from a slog, one bounce into the boundary
turns it with the spin to long-on
slides one into the pads, tickled down to fine leg
down leg side again, nurdled to fine leg to bring up the 200 for Pakistan
flicked wide of midwicket for an easy single
angles a length ball into middle and leg, worked wide of the lone man in the infield at midwicket
cramped for room, chops the length ball to point
forces a length ball outside off to long-off
this one breaks away from off stump, steered wide of point for an easy single. He opened the bat face just a wee bit to find the gap
good take down leg side. Drift and turn takes it past leg stump, kept a touch low as well
no mid-off so he wasn't afraid to go over the top, and he connected well. Overpitched on off, Malik swings cleanly to get the elevation. Hit that off the middle
punched straight to Pollard at midwicket. Nothing mysterious about Narine so far in the series.

That should count as a bonus wicket, against the run of play.  Malik can't believe what he's just done. Shapes to cut, the intention was right, but the execution came a cropper as he skewed a simple catch to Darren Bravo at backward point. For a moment, no one even reacted, such was the mood in the West Indies camp after coming under Malik's sustained attack. This should give them some relief. Narine may have just got the ball to bounce a little more on that occasion as a result of which the ball flew off a thick outside edge.
swept with the spin to fine leg, off the mark immediately
makes a bit of room and cuts that to deep point
welcomed to the crease for a new spell with a delightful extra cover drive. Tossed up nicely, Azam got to the pitch of the ball and crashed that into the gap at sweeper cover. Super touch that
forced off the back foot to deep cover for an easy single, sensible stuff. A boundary followed by a single
steps out to work it leg side but the bat got stuck into his right pad as he looked to turn it wide of midwicket
steps out and smothers the spin
extra bounce this time from a lot fuller on middle, Sarfraz gets back to block
easy single, rocks back and steers it wide of Pollard at cover
takes it on the full and works it down to long on
punched off the back foot to deep midwicket
top edges an attempted paddle onto his face. Ouch, that should hurt
leans forward and eases it into the gap at point for an easy single
there's a big gap between cover and point, Azam picks that with ease as he jogs across for a single

nearly chopped it back onto the stumps. Sarfraz looked to run it down but ended up getting an inside edge that ricocheted off Ramdin's pad onto the stumps. The back foot was inside the crease, so it's an  easy call for the third umpire
flatter one on middle and leg, whipped towards the man at deep square le
steps out but can't get to the pitch of the ball, pushed back to the bowler
chips down the track, takes it on the full and turns it into the gap at deep midwicket, Alzarri does well to come around the ropes to cut that off
slider on middle from wide of the crease, he drops it into the off side with soft hands for a quick single, even someone as swift as Pollard was made to look laggard there
fired into the pads, squeezed to short midwicket, tumbling stop
short, wide and he slaps it off the back foot to sweeper cover
friendly length ball at 120 clicks, whipped wide of midwicket
clever, cheeky...whatever you want to call that. Literally runs this down after the ball had almost passed him. Alzarri cuts that off at third man
defends an incoming delivery to point
floats a length ball into middle, kept a touch low as well, defended to midwicket
pulled into the vacant deep square leg region, Marlon Samuels, who has been a mere spectator for most of the proceedings so far today, is agile and alert
punched down to long-on for an ambled single. Into the nervous 90s. Will that change the way he approaches his innings? Crucial time for Pakistan
drifting into the pads, worked down the ground to long-on, easily done
steps out to go over the top, gets a thick inside edge to long-on
driven inside-out with the spin to long-off
fires a yorker-length delivery outside off, just dabs it to the man coming in from short cover. Looked up and saw his partner was ready to go for the singlee. They completed it quite easily
driven back to Benn, who stops it on his followthrough

nearly chopped that back onto the stumps.  May have missed it by a couple of centimetres. Looked to slap that off the front foot but it wasn't all that short. Deflects off Ramdin's pads towards the leg side
firm push down the gtround to long-on
looks to pull but the ball keeps low to hit him on the thigh pad. He was caught in a tangle as he looked to play a short-arm jab. Was off balance as well. Perhaps tried to hit it too hard
worked down to long-on for an easy single
slides a length ball into the pads, wristed to deep midwicket
saw the batsman giving him the charge and slowed it down to bowl a leg-cutter that cramped the batsman. Sarfraz looked to swung leg side, but didn't connect
full toss on middle and leg, flicked to deep midwicket
slower ball on the stumps, runs it down to long-on
full and on the leg stump channel, clipped off the toes to deep backward square leg
comes down the track and makes some room before flat-batting it to long-on
clipped to deep backward square leg off the toes, easy brace
slightly short of a length outside off, shifts across in his crease and whips it to long-on
full ball on the stumps, no pace on that delivery, tucks it away between midwicket and square leg

gets a harmless fuller delivery outside off, comes forward and eases it down to long-off before jogging through for the single. And that's his second century in two matches. Gets a well-deserved applause and Babar gets down on his knees to soak it in. Good, gritty knock in sapping conditions
tucked to deep midwicket
slower half-tracker outside off, can't bowl that to a batsman on 100. Babar responds with a mighty pull over deep midwicket
turns it away to deep square leg
presses forward and drops it in front of cover-point for the single
short and wide, stays in the crease and slaps it, sweeper cover runs a few inches to his right to field it
very slow ball that is pitched up outside off, he has to reach out for it and swipes at it, does not get too much into the shot. The ball goes uppishly to third man
slower full ball, drills it uppishly to long-on

tucked to midwicket, takes the first run quickly and calls for the second. Babar isn't interested and there is a miscommunication. They eventually don't take it and Sarfaraz has to get back, the throw at the non-striker's end does not hit the stumps
short ball, gets big on him, gets a top edge on the pull and the ball goes to the off side after making contact with the helmet
comes forward and drills it through extra cover for a single
slower ball, gently tucks it to midwicket for an easy single
fuller ball outside off, not very pacy, squeezed out, sweeper cover runs in and fields the ball
short ball, angling in, Sarfaraz clears the front leg and swats it away. Pulls it with authority through deep midwicket

gets down to sweep and the ball hits him on the pad. The umpire doesn't give it and West Indies ask for a review. It was very full and Sarfaraz goes down and tries to sweep. But the ball pings him on the back leg before running away fine on the leg side. The question is whether there was any bat or glove involved. This might be a very good review, as there doesn't seem to be any bat or glove involved. Backfoot is in front of leg stump. Hawk-eye shows that it is missing the stumps, but that was not a bad review at all. Ramdin had asked for it and it isn't easy to pick from that angle
full and wide ball outside off, gets down on one knee and creams it over extra cover

another fuller ball, drills it to extra cover and takes off for the run. The fielder thinks of hurling the ball at the non-striker's end, but decides against doing so after seeing that the batsman is comfortably inside
worked away to midwicket
moves a step or two across as the bowler delivers and creams it over the covers region
looks to go big over long-on but gets the slog off the toe end of the bat and the ball rolls towards mid-on. Lack of pace did him in on that occasion
walks down and Pollard drops it short. Sarfaraz tries to make a late adjustment and tuck it away fine but can't get enough bat on it and the ball goes to the wicketkeeper
fires it outside off, waits in the crease before punching it to long-off
shorter ball, pulls but again there is no pace on that delivery and the ball can only go to the fielder at deep midwicket
full toss outside off, gets down low and sweeps to deep square leg

full and outside off. Azam picks it up from outside off and looks to go big over long-on. But it was the slower ball and he doesn't pick it up. The lack of pace means he can't get enough on that shot and miscues it to the fielder at long-on where Carlos Brathwaite settles under it
short and wide, tries to pull and miscues, he is late to complete the shot and the ball is skewed to mid-off
short of a length outside off, looks to open the face of his bat and slide it down to third man but it is extremely slow and he can't make contact
full toss, flicks it away with the angle to deep midwicket. Pushes Imad for the second and puts in the dive as the throw is fired to the wicketkeeper
shorter ball, pulled away, this time straight to the fielder at deep square leg
full and outside off, stands tall in the crease and drills it straight to mid-off
fuller ball outside off, it is very slow, delivered at 99 kmph, Imad drills it on the bounce down to long-off
walks across to cover the off stump, Pollard bowls it slow and full and on the stumps, Sarfaraz clears his front leg and slogs it to cow corner
advances down the track and the bowler drags his length back, Sarfaraz flat-bats it just wide of long-on and they grab two

walks across the stumps, but Pollard follows him with a slower short ball that is angled in, Sarfaraz swivels around and pulls to fine leg, Narine at the boundary makes a poor effort, tries to put his boot in the line of the ball but ends up kicking it away past the ropes
moves across and gets in position early but Pollard offers him a juicy short ball with enough width to open up his arms. Sarfaraz pulls and the ball goes one bounce over the deep midwicket boundary

backs away and exposes all his stumps, Pollard drops it short and angles it in but Sarfaraz is able to open the face of his bat and slap it away to the third man fence. Poor bowling from Pollard and duly punished
low full toss outside off, driven down the pitch, mid-off runs across and tries to field it but pushes it slightly away with the momentum and that allows the batsmen to take the second run
short ball, pulls but doesn't really get hold of it and the ball goes to midwicket
full toss fired down the leg side, Sarfaraz tries to glance it fine but can't make contact, lets out a cry as he is disappointed with missing out on that one
shorter ball, swivels around and pulls it to short fine leg
full toss on off, Imad swats it and the ball goes to the boundary between long-on and deep midwicket
short ball, pulls it away and deep midwicket cuts it off
fired down the leg side again and called a wide
and another wide. Rolls his fingers over the seam as he tries to bowl a slower ball but doesn't control it well and ends up spraying it short and down the leg side
angled down the leg side, trickles it down to fine leg
full and outside off, drills it down to long-on
very full and wide outside off, jams his bat down as he tries to squeeze it out but can't make any contact. It's just about flirting with the line but is within it. Good ball
cross-batted swipe and the off stump is uprooted. It was on a length and aimed at off stump, Imad goes for a big slog across the line and misses, Holder hits
full and angling in just outside off, uses his wrists to guide it through midwicket
steers it down to short third man and takes a very quick single
fuller ball, rolls his fingers over it, Sarfaraz stabs it to backward point to raise his fifty. What a valuable knock late into the innings!
backs away and swats it away to deep midwicket
slower ball uses his wrists to work it to the square leg region
slower short ball that gets big on the batsman, miscues the pull
short of good length outside off, stays firm in the crease and pulls it away through deep midwicket
backs away and looks to go big over the off side but gets an outside edge and the ball races away to the vacant third man region
bangs it in and gets big on Sarfaraz who can't get hold of the pull shot. Goes on the bounce to backward square leg where Benn fields it

inn2.comm: floated at length on off, pushed to cover
flatter one on middle, punched back to the bowler
this one serves back in to cramp Charles for room, worked into the midwicket region
turned with the angle to square leg. Lot of movement in the air for Imad
slider on off stump, bunted wide of short mid-on for a quick single
fired into middle and leg, touch shorter and so Charles had enough time to work that off the back foot to midwicket
floats one across Charles from over the wicket, defended gently to the off side
sashays down the pitch and has a wild swipe across the line, but could only connect with the humid Sharjah air
hint of width outside off, chopped to gully

not sure if it was a plan to bowl a full-length delivery outside off, but he won't complain as a wicket has come. Charles was nowhere to the pitch of the ball but still went through with a lofted drive, only managed to hit it off the bottom of the bat as Imad Wasim accepted a dolly at cover.
slips that down leg side, moved away a long way after it passed Bravo. Sarfraz was moving to his right but suddenly had to change track to gather that delivery
another full delivery sliding down leg, may have clipped Bravo's pad as he tried to tickle that fine.
attacks the stumps by bowling it full on middle from wide of the crease again, Bravo is solidly behind the line of the ball as he defends
deceived in flight as he looks to flick, was overbalanced as the ball struck his pad. Sliding down leg, however
drifting into middle and leg, he looks to work it wide of midwicket but is late on the shot. Stifled appeal from the bowler, but that was more out of hope than anything else
fired into off stump, chops it to point
sliding into the pads, tucked straight to short fine leg. Pressure building. Release shot coming up?
looks to step out and slog across the line over midwicket, gets a thick inside edge towards square leg instead
shots like those should help. Full, enough width outside off as he leans forward and crashes that past extra cover. Lovely shot
stays inside the crease and opens the bat face to run that down to square third man
looks to work it wide of midwicket but the ball moves away late to take the edge and roll towards point, excellent stop there
hops back into the crease and swivels back to pull, late on the shot as the ball deflected off the glove to fine leg. Amir bowled that at 143 clicks
beaten by a peach that came back in and then deviated ever-so-slightly to shave past the outside edge. Bravo's feet were rooted to the crease as he pushed at that
worked into the deep backward square leg region
good roll of the wrists to fetch that whip from outside off towards square leg
steps out and flicks that tossed up delivery straight to square leg
made room to cut but changed his shot the moment he realised that kept coming back in to cramp him for room. Blocked
steps out but can't get to the pitch of the ball as he looks to swing over midwicket, gets a thick inside edge onto the pad. Imad saw him coming and shortened his length cleverly
slider into middle and leg, tapped to midwicket
timed nicely but short fine runs back to pick that up just before it crossed the boundary
inswing this time, or so it looked, tucked past the infield to deep midwicket
can't take toll of that overpitched delivery, mistimed to mid-off
cleverly done. Short and wide outside off, he played it rather late to glide that past second slip. Third man was too square and had no chance
straightens after pitching on off from around the stumps, he's squared up as he plays that to midwicket
squeezed to backward point, excellent tumbling stop by Imad, who threw himself to his left to pluck that with one hand
turned with the angle, but straight to short fine leg
driven back but straight to mid-off
defends an incoming delivery to the leg side
hit on the pad as he looks to tickle it fine
slowed it down nicely this time, punched back down the ground to mid-on
swung across the line towards the man at wide long-on
drifting into the pads, tickled behind short fine leg, should have been a couple and they get it in the end
once again lucky to get away with a half-volley on the pads, tucked to short fine leg

good length and attacking the stumps, tucks it to midwicket. Mid-on runs across and slides before taking aim at the non-striker's end. Has ample time but only one stump in time. He misses but a direct hit would have sent him back

nasty bouncer! Bravo wasn't expecting that. That just kicks up from the short of good length area and hits Bravo hard on the helmet. He didn't have much time to get away from it and takes his eyes off the ball. The protective layer at the back of the helmet comes flying off
follows it up with a fuller ball that is angled in to the stumps, Bravo comfortably tucks it with the angle behind square. Fine leg is inside the circle and square leg is wide, so he spilts the gap
width on offer and Bravo opens up his arms, slashes at it and gets it to point where it is fielded
what a shot! That had elegance written all over it. It was a fuller ball outside off, Bravo gets his foot across and drives it on the up. Splits the gap in the covers region with surgical precision
knocks it straight to the fielder at cover
runs it down to third man
short of a length ball, on the legs, fine leg is up and Bravo neatly tucks it away, uses the pace on that delivery and trickles it down
that's more like it, good length and on the stumps, Bravo knocks it back to the bowler
slower ball on a length, pushed across, defended cautiously on the front foot down the pitch
fuller and angling away, width on offer, Bravo elegantly punches but straight to the fielder at cover
sprays it down the leg side, it swung a little, Bravo looks to glance it down to fine leg but it drifts away from him and the wicketkeeper can't get to the ball despite putting in the dive
full and on off stump, pushed down the pitch
fuller ball outside off, driven to extra cover
sprays it on the pads, tucked away with the angle but straight to the fielder at short fine leg
short of a length but similar line and angle, tucked away off the hips but again can't beat short fine leg
down the leg side, looks to move away and glance it but can't get bat to ball, the ball goes narrowly past the leg stump
back of a length, pacy delivery, 151 kmph, pushed across, stays in the crease and defends to the off side, loses balance as he finishes delivering that ball
full and on the pads, clipped away to deep midwicket
full and on the pads, knocks it straight to midwicket
short of length delivery outside off, steered straight to point
enough width to steer that one down to third man
rolls his wrists on that to turn it wide of square leg
once again it's short and wide outside off, defended to point. Brathwaite's bottom hand, it seems, is very tightly held to the grip
worked across the line towards midwicket as they steal another single. Azhar Ali won't mind the singles
sliding down leg side, Bravo's plays too early as the ball deflect off the thigh pad towards fine leg
neat little flick off the pads to deep square leg
bangs this one in at length on off, gets some lift off the deck as well, Bravo takes his bottom hand off the grip to tap that towards the off side for a quick single
gets on top of the bounce and nurdles it down to fine leg
stays inside the crease to defend that short of length delivery to the off side
eased down to third man with Wahab's pace for an easy single
squared up by an off-cutter that pitched on length and fizzed away. Brathwaite was committed into playing that and couldn't pull out. Sarfraz collects on the bounce
attempts a drive, but no timing on that whatsoever, straight to mid-off
turns a length ball on middle towards midwicket
bangs a short ball into the batsman from around the stumps, Bravo ducks under that one without a hassle this time
wild swing to that short delivery, gets a top edge that flies over the slip cordon and down to third man. Rush of blood from Bravo
slows it down and gets the ball to hold up on the surface, Bravo checks his shot to bunt that down to point

he's picked the bones out of that one. Shot of the day, I tell you. It was almost he was waiting for that short ball. Swiveled back, got into position early, rolled his wrists over that to keep it down and imperiously pulled him into the square leg boundary
slower length ball outside off, looks to ease it behind point, ends up getting an inside-edge onto the pad
excellent effort at deep backward square leg by Asad Shafiq but he can't stop that whip. Too short and Brathwaite timed it superbly. Used the pace to generate the power and timing
late on the shot. It was banged in short on middle and leg, hit high on the thigh pad as he looked to tuck it behind square on the leg side
rip roaring bouncer on middle, this time Brathwaite gets into position early to get out of the way
slower and fuller outside off, he mistimes a drive straight to cover
short and sliding down leg, he gets a bit of thigh pad while trying to tickle that fine
very full and on the toes, clipped away to backward square leg
pushed through outside off, stays in the crease and knocks it to point
fuller ball on middle and off, pushed to mid-off
good length on leg and middle, opens the face of his bat and works it to backward point
opens the face of his bat again, length ball on leg and middle, knocks it towards point, throw fired at the non-striker's end but misses the stumps
fuller and angling in to the pads, keeps the score ticking by clipping it away to deep square leg
rapped on the pads but it pitched outside leg, it's angled across from around the stumps and Brathwaite gets down to sweep but the ball goes off the pad behind square on the leg side
presses forward and drives to point
comes forward and taps it to the off side. The non-striker wants a run but Bravo sends him back
bowls it full and on the stumps, comes forward and defends
defended down the pitch. No run there
fuller ball outside off, driven towards backward point
drops it short outside off, doesn't bounce much, flat-bats it back to the bowler
flatter and on the stumps, stays in the crease and knocks it back to the bowler
flat and spinning away outside off, punched to mid-off
similar line, length and trajectory, stays in the crease and punches to mid-off
gives it a little bit of air this time and pitches it up, Brathwaite gets forward and eases it down to long-off
angled in on the pads, tries to turn it away to short fine leg, just one off the over again
pushed through quicker from around the stumps, nudged to the leg side
gets down and tries to sweep but it comes in at a tricky angle from around the wicket and he gets a top edge to fine leg
slightly short of a length, backs away but it keeps low, manages to get it away to long-off nonetheless
slaps it to covers
gets down to sweep but it is pitched around the leg stump and hits him on the leg. They don't appeal for lbw as that pitched outside leg
nudges it to the leg side

floated up, gets down to sweep and the ball goes off the toe end of the bat to the deep square leg fence where two fielders converge and team up well as one them slides and pushes it away and the other picks it up
fired down the leg side, Bravo makes no contact on the clip, but it is not given a wide. Probably just about came in contact with the bat
works it down to long-off
stays on the backfoot and flat-bats this short of a length ball past the bowler who dives to his right
pushed through quicker on the stumps, tucked to midwicket
punched off the backfoot to covers
tucked off the pads to square leg
bowls it outside leg, gets down to sweep but can't pierce the fielder at square leg
West Indies are desperate to get a move on. Gets down the track and tries to go big over deep midwicket but he doesn't middle it and it goes squarer. Much-needed boundary nonetheless
turned away to midwicket
stays in the crease and steers it past point, man in the deep runs across and fields it
pushed through quicker from around the stumps, whips it away to long-on from the crease
turns away sharply, tries to whip it to the leg side from outside off and the ball goes uppishly to the right of the bowler who gathers it on the bounce
eased down to long-off. They need to find something here, West Indies. Required rate over 8.5 now. Pkistan won't mind these singles
pitched on middle and leg but spins away sharply and goes down the leg side. Bravo goes for a slog sweep and misses
monster hit down the ground. It was on a length and spun back in to Bravo who makes room and gives it a proper thwack as he lofts it over long-on. The ball seems to have gone out of the stadium

dropped. Bravo tried to go over long-on again. It was flighted nicely outside off and Bravo looked for a mighty slog and goes hard at it. Gets it horribly wrong and skies it to the Pakistan captain at cover. It stayed up for along time but he had enough time to sttle under it, should have been taken
comes forward and defends to the off side
pushed through quicker, defended to the leg side
tucked to midwicket

what a waste of a wicket. It was pushed a long way across and Brathwaite makes room and slaps it away. He sets off for a run but point moves quickly to his right and picks it up. He wanted to fire the throw at the bowler's end but changes his mind and hurls a good throw at the wicketkeeper's end. Brathwaite is sent back and Sarfraz collects it cleanly and whips the bails off. Brathwaite is nowhere to be seen, kicks the turf as he walks off
stays back and defends it towards mid-off
comes forward and bunts it
stays back and looks to flick and misses, hit high on the pad
width on offer, stays in the crease and slaps it but can't pierce the infield
tucked behind square on the leg side
short of a length, stays back in the crease and jabs it back to the bowler
looks to drive and does so with hard hands, gets an outside edge and the ball goes to cover-point
fuller ball, comes forward and drives
flighted and angled in to the stumps, comes forward and looks to push and the ball goes off the inside edge to the leg side

huge hit and that's out of here again. It spins back in from just outside off, the angle is to his liking and he picks the length up early. Hammers it over long-on and the ball goes over the roof and out of the stadium. That was 110 metres! Also brings up his fifty!
turns it away to midwicket
pushed through quicker on the stumps, knocks it back to the left of the bowler who hurries across to gather it
tossed up outside off, drops it in front of cover point and scampers across for the single
pitches outside leg, Samuels comes down the track and makes a late adjustment as it turns sharply and glides it down to fine leg
gives the bowler the charge early again, tucks it to deep square leg this time
floated up outside off, works it away uppishly towards backward point who dives to save it

it's a slightly short delivery and Samuels comes forward with a big backlift before making a late adjustment and tries to defend . He is rapped on the pads and there is an appeal for lbw. Azhar consults with Imad before going for the review. Samuels defended it with his bat very close to pad, but Imad is pretty certain there was no bat. He was a long way down the track. Hawkeye shows that the ball would have clipped the top of leg stumps. Less than 50 percent of the ball hitting, so the on-field umpire's call stays
skips down the track again and defends without fuss to the off side this time
drops it to the off side and takes a quick single by the time the cover fielder can run in and swoop in on the ball. Bravo doesn't run across quickly enough but the throw isn't great
tries to tuck it off the pads but the ball goes off the pads to short fine leg. He nails a direct hit at the non-striker's end but the batsman has made it back

what's happening here. Smauels guides one to short third man and blindly takes off for a single. Bravo isn't interested and sends Samuels back and he has to put in a desperate dive. The throw comes in at the wicketkeeper's end but Sarfraz takes the bails off with his gloves while getting in position to collect the ball
tucked to midwicket
good length on the stumps, turns it away behind square
short of good length outside off, knocks it off the backfoot to covers
length ball outside off, defended off the backfoot
goes for a big shot down the ground but the ball is pacy and nips back in late, miscues it to mid-on
short ball, pulled powerfully to deep square leg where a brilliant stop is made
comes forward and eases it down to long-off
pushed across quicker and flat. Bravo tries to make use of the width on offer and slap but misses

short ball, pitching outside leg, makes no contact on an awkward attempt at a pull shot, had no room to play that shot. He is rapped on the pads and an appeal is made but that pitched outside leg and hit him quite high
pushed back to the bowler

that's the third shot he has played in that arc. It's right in the slot and is pitched up outside off, gets the front foot out of the way which enables him to open up his arms. He hammers it straight down the ground
backs away and slaps one to mid-off
angled in to the pads, tucked away for a single
full and slower on the stumps, Samuels taps it gently and drops it in front of cover and rushes across
short ball, tries to pull on the front foot but the ball bounces steeply and he makes no contact, that's one for the over
short ball again, bounces steeply and Bravo thinks of playing the pull but is forced to pull out and back away after seeing the bounce. Two for the over, says the umpire
punches it wide of point
sprays it down the leg side and Sarfraz has to dive to stop it
attacking line, bang on the stumps, Samuels presents the full face of his bat and taps it to the off side. Point runs in and gathers the ball but the batsmen rush through for the single
short and wide, tries to slap it away but it doesn't bounce as much as he would have liked and makes no contact
length ball, stays in the crease and flat-bats it to mid-off

what an effort from the bowler! Fires a yorker outside leg, Bravo jams his bat down and the ball goes just to the right of him. He takes off for the single and Hasan darts across on his followthrough, slides down, gathers the ball and turns around to nail a direct hit at the striker's end. Took a moment of brilliance to end a fabulous innings
short and wide, backs away and looks to pull but it's a slower ball and the batsman goes through with the shot early

skied to deep extra cover and the fielder misjudges it. Samuels backed away and looked to lift a fuller ball over the in field on the off side but he miscues it and the ball goes very high to the extra cover region. Asad Shafiq runs and tries to get to it but he never seemed to have it under control. Puts in a desperate dive in the end but the ball drops short of him
short of a length, tucked away to midwicket
short and wide, cut away
comes forward and steers it to short third man, Smauels casually jogs the single. Throw is fired at the striker's end but doesn't hit the stumps
pushes it down to long-off
whipped away through midwicket
width on offer, Ramdin slaps it through covers
fired on the pads, nudged to the leg side
acrobatic stop at point, Samuels struck that hard but Rizwan did well to time his jump well to pull off a one-handed stop
slices the low full toss down to Wahab at third man
forced off the back foot to sweeper cover, didn't have much room to work with
swung across the line, manages a healthy top-edge that flies over short fine leg. Runs matter, it's not about how they come at this stage
backs away to slap that over point, but Hasan saw the batsman trying to line him up and slowed it down by bowling that off the back of the hand
low full toss outside off, drilled to cover. Good stop
quicker one on middle, cut straight to the point fielder
worked across the line to long-on
into the gap and four. Saw the ball drifting into his half and he lofted it over midwicket. Timed it well, there was a big gap between long on and deep square, picked to perfection
forceful inside-out drive to wide long-off
good old fashioned slog sweep which he fetches from way outside off, lands in no man's land at deep midwicket. Once again saved by acres of gap on the on side. Didn't get underneath the ball
beaten by a quicker delivery outside off, kept a touch low as well
gets a thick inside edge to short fine leg, he attempted a wild slog over deep midwicket
backs away to punch one into the long-off region
that's a flat hit over long-on. Didn't get underneath the flight but went through with the stroke and struck it well.
backs away to crack that off the back foot to cover, he's moving a lot in the crease, thereby making it difficult for the bowler
swept from outside off towards short fine leg

Rizwan palms that over the fence at deep midwicket.  Samuels didn't get hold of that slog whatsoever, only managed a top edge that should have been taken by the boundary rider. Rizwan was in a couple of paces to make it difficult. Had he been at the ropes, it would have been a regulation catch. No excuses nevertheless, should have been taken. Tried to reverse cup that. Also, the momentum was taking him backwards, which is much more difficult
back away to cut that short ball to point
floats a length ball across the batsman, who is beaten in his attempt to flay that on the up through cover point. Kept a touch low to beat the inside edge
worked off his hip towards midwicket
drops the ball into the off side behind square for a quick single
looks to muscle that length ball over midwicket, bottom edges it to the fielder instead
bottom edges a wild slog across the line, keeper runs to his left to stop that. Could have so easily dragged that back onto the stumps
steps out to slog, gets a thick inside edge down to fine leg. His head was facing the sky when he made contact
backs away to slap that to extra cover, super stop by Azhar at the edge of the circle. That was a certain boundary
muscles the short ball to long-on, one bounce to Shoaib Malik. Lack of bounce meant he couldn't get under that one
flayed straight to cover again
drags the slog from outside off towards long-on
bunted over the bowler's head, Malik at long-on into the picture again
struck firmly towards deep point. Made room to slap that into the gap
excellent bouncer on middle, Samuels gets on top of the bounce to drop that into the off side for a quick single.  28th ODI fifty
looks to go over cover, slices it over mid-off instead, good enough to scamper back for the second
pulled over Wahab's head, mid-off fielder runs back to pull it back in. Ramdin wasn't entirely in control of the slap. He was off balance when ball hit the bat
cramped on the pull, gets it off the top half of the bat, just lobs over Wahab. Hit the bat near the handle and could have been a return catch had Wahab not fallen over in his followthrough.  146kph
dabs it down to third man to keep strike
backs away and slugs a flat hit down to long on
too full outside off, squeezed to extra cover, Ramdin has no choice but to get across to the other end
cramped for room, Samuels is beaten for pace as he backs away to pull. Rolls back to the bowler. Clever from Hasan Ali, controlling his length and pace superbly
slower delivery this time, Samuels was waiting for it inside the crease and then slapped it over cover. There was enough time for him to line himself up before he smashed that
full toss on middle, swung down to wide long-on
that's a fierce hit over midwicket. Too full outside off, Ramdin literally plays a sweep-slog. Took it on the full and generated enough power through his swing, one bounce into the boundary

Sarfraz has put down a tough chance off the bottom edge . Quick ball that kept coming back in to cramp Samuels for room, the keeper was going the right way but the ball was dying on him. Will that prove costly? Only time will tell

no, it doesn't because Wahab has cleaned him up with pace. That was a short of length delivery on middle at 146 kph, it kept a touch low as well, but Samuels was late on it and ended up playing it onto the stumps. Valiant knock, but you got the feeling one good ball was all that was needed at this stage, especially with him swinging come hell or high water. Relief for Pakistan
deflects off the thigh pad towards fine leg
tucked towards midwicket, the fielder was too deep to allow an easy single
defends a rising length ball outside off to point
rip roaring bouncer that nearly raps him on the glove as he tucks it down to fine leg
rising length ball that nips back in to hit the thigh pad, they take a run off the deflection
hops across to play a half-pull to short fine leg
pulled to deep midwicket, Pollard wanted the second but Ramdin wasn't quite sure
backs away and squeezes a yorker-length delivery to mid-off
worked off his hip towards deep square leg

he's cleared the ropes quite comfortably at deep midwicket. This was a slower delivery that went wrong, once again plenty of width which allowed Ramdin to find his swinging arc and make clean connection
keeps coming back in from around the stumps and cramp him for room, ball deflects off the thigh pad to short fine leg

that's the end of Ramdin's party. Done in by sheer pace from Wahab once again. He angles it back in from wide of the crease from around the stumps, it wasn't all that short for Ramdin to pull off the front-foot. He was late on the shot as well and managed a bottom edge to send the leg stump cartwheeling
looks to angle it into his rib cage, but misses his mark and slips it down leg
vociferous appeal for caught behind, but the ball was sliding down leg again. Brathwaite needed to get some bat to tickle that into the fine leg boundary but missed
drilled down the ground, but finds mid-off
he's cracked that into the deep midwicket boundary. Wahab bowls this short, Carlos swings cleanly and hits that in front of square. Was in total control. Spanked that off the middle
hops back to turn that towards square leg
squeezed to backward point as they scamper through for a quick single
length ball, angling in, tucked away to deep square leg
very full ball outside off, jams his bat down and squeezes it out but the ball runs away behind the stumps
fuller ball, driven down to long-off
persists with the full ball on the outside off channel, drags it out to long-on
short of good length ball, mistimes the attempted pull
full toss outside off, slashes hard at it but doesn't really get hold of it, the ball goes on the bounce to sweeper cover
short and angling in, swivels around with the pull but can't middle it, the ball is fielded at short fine leg
tucked to backward square leg
full toss angling in, looks to move away and slog but gets a leading edge and the ball flies past the short third man fielder
gets his front foot out of the way and attempts an almighty slog but doesn't make contact as he is beaten by the pace on that delivery
attempts a similar shot and this time he can make contact as the ball is a lot closer to him, gets it off the inside edge to deep square leg
very full, very wide outside off, clears the front leg and tries the slog but get nowhere near it

short ball outside off, chops the pull shot and the ball comes back to the bowler who gathers it on the followthrough, and, like Hasan Ali earlier, turns back around in a jiffy and nails a direct hit at the striker's end. Carlos Brathwaite, perhaps not expecting Pollard to miscue the pull, had set off for a run and he can't make it back. Another brilliant piece of fielding
short of a length, waits in the crease and knocks it towards mid-on, the bowler darts across on his followthrough and fields it
beaten. Sticks his bat out to a teaser outside off and can't make contact
length ball on off, opens the face of his bat and runs it down to backward point
short ball, it's slower and Pollard goes through with the pull shot early
similar delivery, slow and short outside off, makes no contact on the pull shot
pitched up outside off, gets a good backlift and smacks it powerfully through long-off
worked down to long-on
quicker ball that is wider, Pollard tries to go big over the leg side and miscues the shot to sweeper cover as the ball goes uppishly off the leading edge
works it down to long-on again
tucked to deep midwicket
advances down the track to met the pitch of the ball before powerfully punching it to long-off
backs a long way across, it's quick and fired just outside off, Holder swipes and makes no contact
slower length ball outside off, Holder is beaten by the lack of pace as he looks to open the face of his bat late
taps it gently on the front foot to the vacant areas in the covers region and jogs across for the single
short of a length, Pollard is able to wait in the crease and ride the bounce before tucking it to the leg side

goes for a wide yorker but ends up firing a low full toss outside off, Holder uses his wrists and finds the gap at deep backward point, uses the pace on the delivery and the ball races away to the boundary
drops it in front of short third man
good length, drifting in, tucked with the angle to midwicket
short ball on the stumps, jumps back to ride the bounce and defends it
short of a length, drifting in from outside off, tucked away to deep backward square leg
short ball, uses the angle to pull it over the fielder at fine leg who leaps up but the ball shoots past him. Got enough elevation
goes for the wide yorker and fires a low full toss outside off, driven to extra cover
tries to flick it away but makes no contact and wears it on the pad, thinks of stealing a leg bye but the ball hardly travels on the on side field and Amir is able to quickly get across and gather it
angled in outside off but straightens late, Holder sticks his bat out and is beaten
lets out a grunt as he delivers that, It's short of a length and Holder tucks off the pads through fine leg
taps it to the point region and they jog through the single
short ball outside off, Pollard is pushed back and he defends it off the backfoot back to the bowler
short and wide, mistimes the pull to deep backward square leg
lot of width on offer, waits for it before opening the face of his bat, finds backward point
comes forward and pushes at a full ball outside off, the ball races to the third man fence off the outside edge
knocks it to mid-on
played back to the bowler
whipped to long-on
stays in the crease and tucks it to the leg side, long-on runs up and fields the ball
fuller length outside off, defended to the right of the bowler

dropped. Loopy delivery fired outside off, Pollard tries to loft him down the ground and sends it uppishly to long-on, the fielder there misjudges it and makes a mess of what should have been a fairly straightforward catch
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off
slightly wide delivery outside off, bowls it quicker, Pollard tried to muscle over long-off but skewed it to Malik there who settles under it and takes it easily
fired flat and on the pads, tucked away to the leg side
flat and on a length, defended back to the bowler
blocked to cover
pushed through flat and on off, defended on the front foot to the off side
stays on the backfoot and drops it wide of covers for a single
bowled down the leg side and called a wide
another drop. Narine tries to slog but miscues it to midwicket who spills it. It was hit extremely hard, so tough chance
tucked behind square
fuller ball, driven to extra cover
tries to go big over the leg side and makes no contact
